    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-12-03T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-12-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="1022"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1022">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/3103</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        British Chargé</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_BCAR1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Barclay</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Memorandum</hi>
                </p>
                <p>The Secretary of State presents his compliments to the Charge d’Affaires of Great
                    Britain and has the honor to acknowledge the receipt of his memorandum dated
                    October 31, 1918,<note n="1" xml:id="d1022fn1">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_839">p. 839</ref>.</note>
                    relative to the advisability of taking precautionary measures of a military
                    character with regard to the small states on the western frontier of Russia.</p>
                <p>The Secretary of State has given this matter careful consideration and believes
                    that the situation in these border states should be considered in connection
                    with the general problem of the occupied territory of Russia.</p>
                <closer>
                    <dateline rendition="#left">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-12-03">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 3, 1918</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
